<P><UL>
Architecture Description Languages (ADLs) provide the user the ability to quickly retarget the tool-set (compiler, simulator) to different architectures. </UL></P>
<P><UL>
Objectives (of the ADL):
<UL>
<LI> Be able to specify a wide variety of architectures (VLIWs, DSPs, etc)
<LI> Capture information necessary to do system design space exploration 
<UL>
(i.e. architecture-compiler exploration)
<BR></UL><LI> Capture information necessary to �adapt� optimizations to different architectures.
<LI> Support automatic generation of tool-set.</UL></UL></P>
